<paragraph blockId="11.[794,1389,2645,3067]" pageId="11" pageNumber="522">
Although based on mtDNA, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1896" box="[1245,1389,2758,2791]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="522" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="perrensi">C. perrensi</taxonomicName>
can be classified in the torquatusspecies group; according to biogeography, it has been considered as part of the Corrientes group. Karyotype is 2n = 50, 54, 56 and 58, and sperm form is symmetric. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
