<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="522" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[182,1387,3072,3458]" pageId="11" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[183,434,3072,3105]" pageId="11" pageNumber="522">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Total length 230-270 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Perrens’s Tuco-tuco is medium-sized. General coloris dark buff or clay. Along medial line that extends from face down back, pelage is mixed with black. Under surfaces are rich buff from throat to belly, and upper surfaces of hands and feet have thin white hair. Skull is short skull, broad, and rounded, without many crests; interorbital region is short and wide; and postorbital process is underdeveloped. Upper incisors are opisthodont, forming circle that is smaller than in most other tuco-tucos.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
